OL,4,Coldest-running residential home
OL,6,FAfter seeing casualties from the
OL,7,FFranco-Prussian War (1870-1871) as a
OL,8,Fchild, Edith was moved by the
OL,9,Fsuffering of soldiers and went on to
OL,10,Fstudy medicine in Rome and train as a
OL,11,Fdoctor in London.
OL,13,FShe later established Le Platon Home
OL,14,Fon 1 May 1914, aged 50.
OL,16,FThen known as St Peronilla's Home, the
OL,17,Ffacility opened with three women
OL,18,Fresidents before Spanish nuns came to
OL,19,Fhelp Edith run the home in 1920.
